<br>
You have no @#%$ idea what you are talking about! The force powers in JK were a novelty, in JK2 they're well thought-out, effective, and so damn useful and fun.<br>
<br>
Jedi Knight 2 is the most fun I've had single player in a LONG time. There is nothing like knocking down a bunch of storm troopers with force push then hacking them into little pieces or even better pulling their weapons out of their hands then chasing them down as they run about like rabbits. The lightsaber fights are just beautiful - they're so damn acrobatic it's like a high-speed lethal ballet sometimes - Finish a fight with a reborn by flipping over their heads and chopping them from above <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> without</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> whooping for joy if you can.<br>
<br>
The puzzles are tricky but rewarding, I mean damn, you want plain sailing? Go play a gimpy game - the hints are there, you just have to look for them. I am incredibly impressed by JK2, just a shame they didn't do the same thing with the cutscenes that they did from Jedi Knight - ingame engine cutscenes don't really cut it.<br>
<br>
